<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="74" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="74">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="74">This species can be easily recognized by the teeth on the caudoventral margin of the male pygofer, the aedeagal shaft broadened gradually from the base to the end, the lateral triangular expansions on shaft apex, and the dorsal connective with the process from the inner ventral margin weakly sclerotized, slender, short and unbranched.</paragraph>
